Ben Hamed Kon (born November 2, 1987 in Abidjan) is an Ivorian football player who currently plays for Gainare Tottori. His mazzy dribblings during his time at Home United FC caught many Singaporeans by surprise.[1] Kon plays as Attacking Midfielder, Left Winger or Striker. He's one of the up and coming young talent, rumours surfaced that Newcastle United and Stoke City are monitoring him closely.  
